  "text": "March 24, 2025 PIN Architects has shared photos of a small modern cabin they completed in Turkey, that’s located on the slopes of a deep valley surrounded by rocky cliffs and olive trees. The cabin, entirely made of steel, has facades that are fully glass, with solid wall applications in a few areas where needed. The cabin is also surrounded by a terrace and eaves, making it possible to walk around the entire exterior. The interior space measures just over 800 square feet (75sqm) and includes a living space, kitchen, bathroom, and a bedroom, along with a niche for dressing and other storage needs. The living area consists of a kitchen, bathroom and closet behind it, and a bedroom connected by corridors on both sides of the house, completing a rectangular layout. Photographs: Ibrahim Ozbunar | Architect: PIN Architects | Lead Architects: Salih Kucuktuna, Fikret Sungay, Ekin Arslan Bahceci, Batuhan Demirkaya, Caglar Biber | General Constructing: Evv Yapi Uretim",
